---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SearchBox from '../../components/SearchBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Search"
    description="Search the LSCSS documentation"
>
    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="site-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Search</p>

            <h1>
                Search documentation
            </h1>

            <p class="intro">
                Find methodology, examples, comparisons, debugging help, and
                the answer to the CSS problem currently ruining your afternoon.
            </p>
        </section>

        <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Search sections">
            <a href="#search-box">Search</a>
            <a href="#common">Common searches</a>
            <a href="#routes">Quick routes</a>
        </nav>

        <section id="search-box" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Search the docs
            </h2>

            <p>
                Search by problem, not only by page name. Good examples:
                specificity, modifiers vs state, utility classes, base layer,
                legacy CSS, @scope, container queries.
            </p>

            <SearchBox />
        </section>

        <section id="common" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Common searches
            </h2>

            <div class="hub-card-grid">
                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/decision-trees/">Should this be a utility or component?</a></h3>
                    <p>Use the decision trees for utilities, theme, state, and hacks.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/specificity-visualiser/">Why is this selector winning?</a></h3>
                    <p>Check layers, specificity, :where(), and scope before reaching for important.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/base-styles/">Where should this global style live?</a></h3>
                    <p>Reset rules, typography, and document defaults belong in the right layer.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="routes" class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Quick routes
            </h2>

            <div class="hub-card-grid">
                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/methodology/">I am learning the system</a></h3>
                    <p>Start with layers, naming, architecture, and core methodology.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/migration/">I inherited legacy CSS</a></h3>
                    <p>Improve old systems without rewriting everything for sport.</p>
                </article>

                <article class="hub-card">
                    <h3><a href="/comparisons/">I need to compare approaches</a></h3>
                    <p>Compare LSCSS with BEM, Tailwind, CSS Modules, and @scope.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
